page.title: 07ECOLOGY
page.content: ECOLOGY. Although not far from a large city and in a good farming area there was some evidence of wild life . In the fields were fox holes and footprints in many mud patches. A wet early summer meant that the landscape was very green.There were many magpies,crows and cuckoos.Rabbits and their burrows were seen at Primrose Cottage.Butterflies(Red Admiral,Painted Lady and Cabbage White) were seen.Wild flowers were in abundance ,including Buttercups ,Poppies ,Dogroses ,Moondaisies and elderflower
